    %article#the-pursuit-of-happyness-2006
      %h2 The Pursuit of Happyness
      %p.metadata
        A 2006 American biographical film directed by Gabriele Muccino about the on and off-homeless salesman-turned-stockbroker Chris Gardner.
        %a{:href => "http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0454921/", :title => "The Pursuit of Happyness (2006) on IMDb"} IMDb
        %a{:href => "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Pursuit_of_Happyness", :title => "The Pursuit of Happyness on Wikipedia"} Wikipedia
      %figure
        %img{:alt => "Screencap of Chris who tells Mr. Twistle how he thinks the cube works. The angle is set so, that Chris is at the back and Mr. Twistle is in front.", :src => "images/rubiks-cube-the-pursuit-of-happyness.jpg"}
          %figcaption
            Chris explains to Mr. Twistle how he thinks the cube works.
            %small Copyright Columbia Pictures Corporation, 2008
      %section.appearance
        %h3 Appearance
        %p
          Chris Gardner
          %small (Will Smith)
          is trying to get a internship to become a stockbroker at
          %em Dean Witter Reynolds
          A scene where Chris solves a Rubik's cube plays a key role in Chris' attempts to get real contact with Mr Twistle
          %small (Brian Howe)
          Important to note is that this movie takes place in the year 1981. The Rubik's cube appears in the following scenes:
        %ol
          %li
            Chris finds a Rubik's cube in the kitchen while having supper with his wife Linda
            %small (Thandie Newton)
            and son Christopher
